{"task_id": "bad_002", "category": "nonsense", "prompt": "Explain the color of number 7 in detail.", "output": "Numbers do not have intrinsic colors, so “the color of 7” depends on the framework you mean. There are a few plausible interpretations:\n\n1. Synesthesia\nSome people with grapheme-color synesthesia automatically experience numbers as specific colors. For one person, 7 might be green; for another, yellow, red, or black. There is no universal mapping.\n\n2. Cultural or symbolic associations\nPeople often assign symbolic colors to numbers:\n- 7 is frequently associated with gold, violet, deep blue, or white.\n- Gold can reflect ideas like luck, sacredness, or perfection.\n- Deep blue or violet may be used because 7 is often linked to mystery, spirituality, introspection, and depth.\n\nExamples:\n- Seven days of creation/rest traditions\n- Seven classical planets\n- Seven notes, seven colors of the rainbow\nThese associations can push people toward rich, “special” colors.\n\n3. Numerology-style interpretations\nIn numerology, 7 is often described as analytical, spiritual, private, wise, and contemplative. If converted into color symbolism, people may choose:\n- Purple/violet: spirituality, wisdom\n- Indigo/deep blue: introspection, intellect\n- Silver: subtlety, intuition\n\n4. Design and branding contexts\nIf you are assigning a color to the numeral 7 in a chart, game, or visual system, the best choice depends on purpose:\n- Blue: calm, trustworthy, clear\n- Purple: mystical, premium, imaginative\n- Gold: rare, important, lucky\n- Red: strong, urgent, attention-grabbing\n\n5. Mathematics\nIn mathematics, 7 has no color. It is simply an integer: odd, prime, positive, and often considered aesthetically notable, but color is not a mathematical property.\n\nIf you want a direct descriptive answer, the most common “poetic” color for 7 is probably deep violet or indigo: a dark, thoughtful, slightly mysterious color suggesting wisdom, distance, and spiritual depth.\n\nIf you want, I can also give:\n- a scientific answer,\n- a synesthetic/artistic answer,\n- or a mythology/numerology-based answer.", "expected_keywords": [], "notes": "nonsense reasoning", "request_id": "por-live-bad_002", "model": "gpt-5.4", "task_integrity": 1.0, "hedging_score": 0.667, "contradiction_score": 1.0, "token_overlap": 0.027, "length_ratio_drift": 1.0, "semantic_proxy_drift": 0.579, "raw_quality_score": 0.504, "raw_success": false, "silence": true, "no_control_success": false, "with_control_success": false, "raw_success_threshold": 0.55, "silence_threshold": 0.3}
