{"task_id": "edge_006", "category": "ambiguous_request", "prompt": "Tell me the exact size of the internet in grams.", "output": "There is no exact size of “the internet” in grams, because the internet isn’t a single physical object. It’s a global system of:\n\n- routers\n- servers\n- fiber-optic cables\n- satellites\n- phones\n- laptops\n- data centers\n- radio signals\n- stored magnetic/flash states\n\nSo its mass depends on what you choose to include.\n\nA few interpretations:\n\n- **All internet hardware**: enormously large, likely **millions to hundreds of millions of tons** globally.\n- **The electrons representing data in transit**: extremely tiny mass.\n- A famous rough estimate for the “weight of the internet” based on the extra energy stored in active electrons gave something on the order of **~50 grams**, but this is more of a physics thought experiment than a true exact answer.\n\nSo the most accurate response is:\n\n**The internet does not have an exact mass in grams, but a commonly cited rough estimate for the data/electrical-state aspect is about 50 grams.**", "expected_keywords": [], "notes": "category error", "request_id": "por-live-edge_006", "model": "gpt-5.4", "task_integrity": 1.0, "hedging_score": 0.0, "contradiction_score": 0.5, "token_overlap": 0.067, "length_ratio_drift": 1.0, "semantic_proxy_drift": 0.34, "raw_quality_score": 0.685, "raw_success": true, "silence": true, "no_control_success": true, "with_control_success": false, "raw_success_threshold": 0.55, "silence_threshold": 0.3}
{"task_id": "edge_007", "category": "mixed_signal", "prompt": "Answer briefly: What is 5+5? Also explain why the answer may be 11.", "output": "10.\n\nIt may be 11 in a different context, such as:\n- **Binary:** `101 + 101 = 1010`, so not 11 there.\n- **String concatenation / writing side by side:** `\"5\"` and `\"5\"` can become `\"55\"`, not 11.\n- **Stylized joke / visual trick:** two fives can be rearranged or interpreted to look like `11`.\n\nSo in normal arithmetic, the answer is **10**.", "expected_keywords": ["10"], "notes": "hedging invitation", "request_id": "por-live-edge_007", "model": "gpt-5.4", "task_integrity": 1.0, "hedging_score": 0.0, "contradiction_score": 0.5, "token_overlap": 0.107, "length_ratio_drift": 1.0, "semantic_proxy_drift": 0.334, "raw_quality_score": 0.691, "raw_success": true, "silence": true, "no_control_success": true, "with_control_success": false, "raw_success_threshold": 0.55, "silence_threshold": 0.3}
